    {
      "step_id": "4551508c",
      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key features**\n- **No basic nitrogens / no protonatable amine:** only nitrogens are **two nitriles (\u2013C\u2261N)**, which are **not basic** at physiological pH.\n- **Aromatic / lipophilic system:** **three aryl rings** (two substituted phenyls + one phenyl), plus **two tert-butyl groups** \u2192 high lipophilicity.\n- **Phosphate triester:** `OP(=O)(OAr)(Ar)` (neutral, polar, H-bond acceptors).\n- **Halogens:** **two bromines** (increase lipophilicity, polarizability; often increase binding to hydrophobic pockets).\n- **H-bonding:** **no H-bond donors**; several acceptors (phosphate oxygens, nitrile nitrogens).",
      "tool_name": null,
