      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition**\n- Typical CYP2D6 inhibitors often have a **basic tertiary amine** (or similar protonatable center) plus an aromatic region (quinidine-like motif).  \n- This molecule **lacks the key basic center**.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
