      "step_index": 7,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Competitive inhibition** of CYP2D6 typically involves positioning an aromatic moiety near the heme and stabilizing binding via the **basic N salt-bridge**/electrostatic interaction.\n- This compound could still enter the active site due to its hydrophobic surface, but would rely on **weaker interactions** (van der Waals, \u03c0\u2013\u03c0) and **H-bond accepting** contacts from phosphate/nitrile\u2014generally **less potent/less selective** for CYP2D6 inhibition.\n- It also lacks obvious **mechanism-based inhibition motifs** (e.g., certain amines that form metabolic-intermediate complexes); nitriles/phosphate triesters are not classic CYP2D6 MBI triggers.",
